result.execSummary:
The defendant Brandon L Redd was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Brandon L Redd in court with attorney Justin Singleton.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
cab
As to counts 1 and 2:
  Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing. 
 Court sentenced the defendant to serve 8 months in the House of Correction as to count 1 and 2 months in the House of Correction as to count 2, consecutive,  with credit for 2 days served.  Court STAYED both sentences and placed the defendant on probation for 18 months, concurrent,  with the following conditions:
- Serve 60 days in the House of Correction; STAYED pending review.
- Complete batterer's intervention program.
- AODA assessment; comply with any treatment.
- Maintain absolute sobriety; random urine screens.
- Attend treatment and/or counseling as determined.
- No contact with victim unless approved by the court.
- Obtain/maintain employment.
- No contact with firearms.
- Pay DV surcharge plus all other costs and surcharges; civil judgment if not paid.
- Pay supervision fees.

Defendant Brandon L Redd in court PRO SE.  Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Defendant does not qualify for public defender representation. Court conducted Indigency Hearing. Court found defendant is eligible for appointment of counsel by court. Court held colloquy with defendant. Defendant requested court appointed counsel and agreed to reimburse Milwaukee County for the expense. The court appointed Atty. Justin Singleton, present in court, to represent defendant in this matter at County expense and at the rate of $60.00 per hour. The court ordered the defendant repay the County at a rate of $50.00 per month beginning the 1st of the month after the completion of the case, and then the 1st of each month there after. Court advised defendant failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Signed, Distributed & Filed, Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense. All conditions of bail remain in effect. Defense requests a Status Conference. Court granted defense request. Case is adjourned for a Status Conference in branch 23.  Status conference scheduled for June 18, 2015 at 08:30 am.
